

1) Define the product scope

Goal: An interactive Streamlit dashboard that:
	•	lets a user choose a set of World Bank indicators (e.g., GDP per capita, life expectancy, CO₂ per capita, school enrollment)
	•	chooses a year (or a range, like “latest available”)
	•	clusters countries based on those features
	•	shows the clusters in 2D (PCA/UMAP), in a table, and optionally on a world map

MVP screens
	•	Sidebar: indicator picker, year picker, missing-data strategy, scaling toggle, clustering algorithm + parameters
	•	Main: cluster scatterplot (2D), cluster summary table, country drill-down

⸻

2) Data access approach (don’t scrape the HTML)

2.1 Country list

Use the Country endpoint to list countries/economies and their metadata (region, income level, etc.).  ￼
	•	Endpoint: https://api.worldbank.org/v2/country?format=json
	•	Filter out aggregates if needed (the API includes aggregate “regions” too: you’ll typically exclude those for country clustering).

2.2 Indicator time series per country

Use the Indicators API (v2) to fetch indicator values.  ￼
	•	Pattern: https://api.worldbank.org/v2/country/{country}/indicator/{indicator}?format=json
	•	You can constrain dates: ...&date=2015:2024
	•	Handle pagination (World Bank API often paginates).

2.3 Licensing / attribution

World Bank indicator pages typically state licensing (commonly CC BY 4.0) and sources: include an “About / Sources” section in the app that links to the indicators used.  ￼

