5) Streamlit app architecture

5.1 Repo structure
	•	app.py (Streamlit entry)
	•	wb_client.py (World Bank API client: country list, indicator fetch, pagination)
	•	features.py (build feature matrix, missing handling)
	•	models.py (scaling, clustering, PCA)
	•	viz.py (plots, tables)
	•	data_cache/ (optional local parquet cache)

5.2 Caching and performance

Use Streamlit caching aggressively:
	•	Cache country list (rarely changes)
	•	Cache raw indicator pulls keyed by (indicator, date_range)
	•	Cache feature matrix keyed by (indicator_set, year, missing_strategy)

This avoids re-downloading on every widget change.

5.3 UI layout (recommended)

Sidebar
	•	Country filters: region, income level (from metadata)
	•	Indicator multi-select (and presets)
	•	Year selector + “latest available” toggle
	•	Preprocessing: scaling, log-transform, missing strategy
	•	Clustering: algorithm, K (or threshold)

Main
	•	KPI row: # countries included, # indicators, % missing removed
	•	Scatterplot (PCA 2D) + cluster legend
	•	Cluster summary table (mean/median of features per cluster)
	•	Country drill-down (select a country → show its indicator time series)

