6) Implementation steps (sequence)
	1.	Prototype the World Bank API client
	•	get_countries() from the country endpoint  ￼
	•	get_indicator(country, indicator, date_range) using v2 endpoints  ￼
	•	Pagination support
	2.	Build the feature-matrix builder
	•	Input: indicator list + year mode (“specific year” or “latest”)
	•	Output: clean dataframe ready for clustering
	3.	Add preprocessing
	•	missing handling
	•	scaling + optional log transforms
	4.	Add clustering + PCA
	•	return labels, cluster centers (if applicable), PCA coordinates
	5.	Create Streamlit UI
	•	sidebar controls → recompute pipeline
	•	interactive plots + tables
	6.	Add attribution panel
	•	show indicator names, codes, and links
	•	cite license/source note behavior (per indicator page)  ￼
	7.	Deployment
	•	Streamlit Community Cloud or any container host
	•	Store secrets if needed (World Bank API generally doesn’t require keys for Indicators)

